Frank: "pshh, no"
Kid: "oh"...and ran away

SoOOo then I was with lauren and emily later on...and they were screamin...So lauren was just like "Simma down" lmao...funny funny

And today was mother goose day...So each group got a rhyme and they had to act it out...Lauren got Humpty Dumpty...and that was hard to do...They all had to act it out...Sean and Lauren were both more nervous then their kids, it was pretty funny...Frank's group won the contest...which it was his 3rd sraight year winning...but one of the kids was like beat boxing, it was soOooO cute!!!

Then at dismissal...Jenny was like loosin her voice, and i said something so i had to clear my throat...which lead to "Let me clear my thoat!"...

SoOoO yeahh..today was pretty interesting...

soOoO...Today was Halloween...So Me, Lauren, Kathleen, Cara, Frank, Emily, Caitie, and Sean all dressed up as cowgirls and cowboys...I was orange...And my flip flops were a size too big because old navy only had 10's in orangeish flip flops lol....So yeahh we're all getting out of the cars and Lauren's great comment: "Emily dun got no gun" lmao...she was really getting into it...  

I had to go to the library in the morning...That was pretty interesting, with a kid who said he was going to quit camp, and refused to go into the library... Then the kids were really like bein rude to the lady that was reading to them... but oOO well

When we got back we took some pictures..."Prom style!!!"...I can't wait to get them developed!!

In the afternoon I went on the nature walk with emily & Lauren...We got lost, kinda, so that was fun lol...and a kid on a bike came out of nowhere and scared the crap out of me and lauren...it was really scary...and then sean came running from nowhere, which was really weird...My delayed goodbye hah. 

At dismissal..."HOI!"...lmao, that was hilarious!!. Then Frank was asking Cara to lift up her skirt, so that the drivers would notice her, lmao. 

AhHh then leaving, lauren gave me a ride home, and we were leavin behind "him" so I waved...and we weren't sure if he saw me, but he did, and when he was pullin out he turned around and waved, lmao, he's so hott!! but his voice is soOoo deep..."Kick him in the balls, and then he'll be like HOI!" hah lmao

..So yeahh today was fun...

Today I was at front desk with mike...That was pretty boring...Me and Makenzie had a talk about how some people piss us off...like "jr."...Then I had traffic with Mike..That was pretty interesting...We got a cop to do traffic for us, John went by and yelled at me...and then Joe went by a little later, and I suposidly gave him a dirty look, but Ooo well...

After everything was done, Me, Cara, and Kathleen went over to Party City to get some stuff for tuesday....it's halloween day, so we're beeing cowgirls//boys...Lauren met us there, and we were goin back to my house to get some more money...and we saw this amazingly HOTT guy...we were like in the middle of a conversation and just completly stopped talking, and like watched him go by, and he was lookin back at us...wow, he was hott lol. So we went to the mall..got some more clothes...And we were on our way to A.C. moore for bandanas and these hott guys in a yellow car were following us, so i made a "smooth move" and turned to look at them...and they saw me, and all started laughin...lmao...I'll never look at a yellow car the same way lol. So she dropped me off at provisions, and everyone was making fun of me cuz of my sunburn...It huts like a bitch, but Ooo well...

kk, So me and lauren decided to start up our livejournals again for the summer b.c of all the funny things that go on...

 

Quote of the day:: "I need to murder some kids"
...Camp started again on tuesday...But we havent had a full day until today due to the rain//lightning ((..??)) storms....So today was our first full day...and there were ALOT of kids...and I was up with the 6&7 year olds today...and they have to pee alot...lol...But lauren was nice and was looking for the other c.i.t's to bring them down, so I wouldnt have to...We talked about last year and my brilliant comments like: "we should cut down all the trees so that the wind will stop"...wow. Then the little Italian kid..."hey you!" lmao, that was hilarious. I got sun burn..The farmers tan is starting!! whoot!! lol.

And then I went to work at provisions...stupid old people...gus's "hi, how are you" voice...Yeah that makes me feel special!! lol

So now Im really tireddd....so...night!!!

<FONT size=1>It's times like these, that I wish I had normal feelings...And saw certain things just like everybody else....I'm constantly wondering- why do I have to be the one faced with all of this, and have to worry about my "image". I hate it, but at the same time I love it, It gives me a reason to keep going, and to keep fighting for what I want, and everytime I try hard, I get the satisfaction of what I want and it makes me so happy. But when I get further away, and go against "her" then I get disappointed, and "she" lets me down once again, into a feeling that is so terribly hard to get out of...and leads me to do things that aren't always the "healthy" way out. I see people making fun of "her" and it makes me think that they have no respect at all for the people who have been faced with everything "she" brings, and the stugles that they go through. Some people just blurt things out without thinking, It's <U>not</U> something to be made fun of, it's <U>serious</U> and alot of people will never understand, until they know somebody who is going through it, and see their strugles...To me "she" is my best friend, "she" has been there for me, when people haven't, "she" give me something to think about when I'm bored, "she" is always in the back of my mind, telling me what to do, and I love "her"...</FONT>

Suicide is not the answer!

Ask the 25-year-old who tried to electrocute himself. He lived. But both his arms are gone.

What about jumping? Ask John. He used to be intelligent, with an engaging sense of humor. That was before he leaped from a building. Now, he's brain-damaged and will always need care. He staggers and has seizures. He lives in a fog. But, worst of all, he KNOWS he used to be normal.

What about pills? Ask the 12-year-old with extensive liver damage from an overdose. Have you ever seen anyone die of liver damage? You turn yellow. It's a hard way to go.

What about a gun? Ask the 24-year-old who shot himself in the head. Now he drags one leg, has a useless arm and has no vision or hearing on one side. He lived through his "foolproof" suicide. You might too.

But ... who will clean your blood off the carpet or scrape your brains from the ceiling? Commercial cleaning companies may refuse that job--but SOMEONE has to do it.

Who will have to cut you down from where you hung yourself or identify your bloated body after you've drowned? Your father? Your mother? Your wife? Your son?

The carefully worded "loving" suicide note is of no help. Those who loved you will NEVER completely recover. They'll feel regret and an unending pain.

Suicide is contagious. Look around your family. Look closely at the 4 year old playing with his cars on the rug. Kill yourself tonight, and he may do it ten years from now.

You DO have other choices. There are people who can help you through this crisis. Call a hotline. Call a friend. Call a family member. Call your minister or priest. Call a doctor or hospital. Call the police. They will tell you that there's hope. Maybe you'll find it in the mail tomorrow. Or in a phone call this weekend. But what you're seeking could be just a minute, a month, or a day away.

You say you don't want to be stopped? Still want to do it? -- Well, then, I may see you in the psychiatric ward later. And we'll work with whatever you have left.

Remember: Suicide is a permanent solution to a temporary problem.
